{"lemma":"عادَة","slug":"عادَة","root":"ع.#.د","root_slug":"ع-_-د","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-_-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adv","name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n30940"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"custom, habit, manner, wont"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"law"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"customary gift or present"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"menses, menstruation"},{"pos":"adv","gloss":"usually, normally, customarily, ordinarily, habitually"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Adah"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare عَادَ (ʕāda, “to return, go back”).\n\nAdverbial accusative of عَادَة (ʕāda, “custom”)."},"ipa":["/ʕaː.da/","/ʕaː.da.tan/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30940","headword_ar":"عَادَةٌ","root":"Ewd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A custom, manner, habit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wont;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daA^obN","text_ar":"دَاْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"watiyrapN","text_ar":"وَتِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (MA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dayodanN","text_ar":"دَيْدَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) so called because one returns to it time after time: it respects more especially actions; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurofN","text_ar":"عُرْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", sayings; as in indicated in the Telweeh &c.; or, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EurofN","text_ar":"عُرْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAdapN","text_ar":"عَادَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are syn.: (MF, TA:) and accord. to El-Mufaddal, [↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiydN","text_ar":"عِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAdapN","text_ar":"عَادَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for he says that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAdaniY EiydiY","text_ar":"عَادَنِى عِيدِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAdatiY","text_ar":"عَادَتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My habit returned to me:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but see the next preceding paragraph, first sentence]: (L, TA:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAdapN","text_ar":"عَادَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAdaAtN","text_ar":"عَادَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAdN","text_ar":"عَادٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,) or rather this is a coll. gen. n., (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiydN","text_ar":"عِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K, TA,) mentioned by Kr, but not of valid authority, (L, TA,) [app. a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiyadN","text_ar":"عِيَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiwajN","text_ar":"حِوَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAjapN","text_ar":"حَاجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawaAy^idu","text_ar":"عَوَايِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAy^iju","text_ar":"حَوَايِجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAjapN","text_ar":"حَاجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but, accord. to Z and others, this last is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAy^idapN","text_ar":"عَايِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", not of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAdapN","text_ar":"عَادَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["MA","K","MF","TA","L","S","O","Msb"]}]}}